Message.MsgText: WARN_OVERLAPPING_MAPPING_CWSIL0009=CWSIL0009W: Overlapping mapping for profile {0} was removed due to profile {1}.
Message.Explanation: Overlapping profiles are not registered to avoid duplicate messages. Messages will not be lost as a result of this removal.
Message.UserResponse: Remove the overlapping profile from the configuration.

Message.MsgText: INFO_DELETE_OK_AFTER_UNSUBSCRIBE_CWSIL0023=CWSIL0023I: Allocated storage space for the broker profile associated with MQ link UUID {0} and broker queue manager {1} was successfully released after successful unsubscription processing.
Message.Explanation: It was not initially possible to release allocated storage space associated with the broker profile, but the successful completion of unsubscription processing for the profile has now allowed the storage space to be released.
Message.UserResponse: No action is necessary

Message.MsgText: WARN_DUPLICATE_MAPPING_CWSIL0008=CWSIL0008W: The duplicate mapping for profile {0} was removed.
Message.Explanation: Only a single profile is registered for each topic in one direction to avoid duplicate messages. Messages will not be lost as a result of this removal.
Message.UserResponse: Remove the duplicate mapping from the configuration.

Message.MsgText: ERR_SINGLELEVEL_WILDCARD_CWSIL0010=CWSIL0010E: The topic for mapping {0} contains a single level wildcard, which is not supported.
Message.Explanation: The only wildcard supported is # at the end of a topic.
Message.UserResponse: Update the configuration to use valid topics.

Message.MsgText: ERR_EB_RESPONSE_COMMAND_CWSIL0016=CWSIL0016E: The response message received from the event broker {0} contained unexpected command {1} ({2}). The response corresponds to mapping profile {3}.
Message.Explanation: Only responses to register and deregister subscriptions are expected from the event broker.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: INVALID_ATTRIBUTE_CWSIL0012=CWSIL0012E: The attribute {1} to value {2} for object of type {0} cannot be set.
Message.Explanation: The attribute value has been ignored.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: ERR_EB_MESSAGE_CWSIL0002=CWSIL0002E: A message received from the event broker {0} was neither a publication nor a response to a command. The message received was of type {1} and corresponds to profile {2}
Message.Explanation: Only responses to register and deregister subscriptions and publication messages are expected from the event broker.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: WARN_INSUFF_STREAMQUEUE_DATA_FOR_REPLY_CWSIL0020=CWSIL0020W: It is not possible to set up automatic routing of reply messages due to a missing broker input queue name on topic mapping {0}
Message.Explanation: The broker input queue name is required to automatically route reply messages. This warning may be ignored if reply messages are not required.
Message.UserResponse: The administrator must correctly fill in the broker input queue name in the named topic mapping.

Message.MsgText: ERR_MULTILEVEL_WILDCARD_CWSIL0011=CWSIL0011E: The topic for mapping {0} contains a multi-level wildcard in the middle, which is not supported.
Message.Explanation: The only wildcard supported is # at the end of a topic.
Message.UserResponse: Update the configuration to use valid topics.

Message.MsgText: TOPICSPACE_DOESNOT_EXIST_CWSIL0019=CWSIL0019E: The topic mapping could not be activated because topic space {0} does not exist. The mapping profile is {1}.
Message.Explanation: Topic spaces referenced by topic mappings should be created explicitly to create a mapping.
Message.UserResponse: Create the missing topic space.

Message.MsgText: ERR_EB_DEREGSUB_FAIL_CWSIL0003=CWSIL0003E: A subscription could not be deregistered on event broker {0} for profile {1} due to reason code {2}.
Message.Explanation: The reason code was returned by an event broker.
Message.UserResponse: Refer to the WebSphere MQ Event Broker Programming Guide for explanation of the reason code. For further information on resolving this error, consult the IBM WebSphere Application Server Support Web site available at: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/support.html. The site provides searchable databases of technotes, solutions, and e-fixes. Information on contacting the WebSphere Support team is also provided.

Message.MsgText: ERR_EB_RESPONSE_MISMATCH_CWSIL0018=CWSIL0018E: Correlation ID {2} received in a response message from the event broker {0} does not match the expected correlation ID {1} for profile {3}.
Message.Explanation: The correlation ID for responses to commands from event broker should match the correlation ID specified in the command.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: ERR_MISSING_TOPIC_CWSIL0006=CWSIL0006E: A message received from event broker {0} for publishing did not contain a topic. The message received was of type {1} and corresponds to profile {2}.
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: ERR_TOPIC_MANGLING_CWSIL0007=CWSIL0007E: Topic mangling is not supported in this version. Inconsistent topics were specified for inbound and outbound profiles in the mapping {0}.
Message.Explanation: Inbound and outbound profiles should specify the same topics.
Message.UserResponse: Modify the mapping profiles to use same topics for both inbound and outbound profiles.

Message.MsgText: TEMPORARY_CWSIL9999=CWSIL9999E: {0}
Message.Explanation: If the message does not give sufficient information, check previous messages for further help.
Message.UserResponse: See previous messages for further information.

Message.MsgText: WARN_EB_RESPONSE_NOCOMMAND_CWSIL0017=CWSIL0017W: A response message received from the event broker {0} did not specify a command. The response corresponds to mapping profile {1}.
Message.Explanation: Only full responses containing request details of register and deregister subscriptions are expected from the event broker.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: WARN_SUBSCRIPTIONS_STILL_ACTIVE_CWSIL0022=CWSIL0022W: It was not possible to release allocated storage space for the broker profile associated with MQ link UUID {0} and broker queue manager {1} because active subscriptions remained after an unsubscribe attempt.
Message.Explanation: A broker profile was not completely deleted when the user issued a deletion request, because active subscriptions remained associated with the broker profile following an automatic attempt to unsubscribe the active subscriptions.
Message.UserResponse: Restart the MQ link that the broker profile is associated with, the remaining persistent state will be deleted during the restart process.

Message.MsgText: ERR_INCOMPLETE_MAPPING_CWSIL0013=CWSIL0013E: The following incomplete topic mapping has been provided - {0}.
Message.Explanation: All mandatory fields should be filled in for topic mappings.
Message.UserResponse: Complete the topic mapping configuration.

Message.MsgText: ERR_JS_EB_PUBLISH_CWSIL0004=CWSIL0004E: A message of the unsupported type {0} was received from topic space {1} on the topic {2} but could not be republished.
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: ERR_EB_JS_PUBLISH_CWSIL0005=CWSIL0005E: A message of type {1} from event broker {0} could not be published. The message corresponds to profile {2}.
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: WARN_ACTIVE_SUBSCRIPTIONS_ON_DELETE_CWSIL0021=CWSIL0021W: Allocated storage space for the broker profile associated with MQ link UUID {0} and broker queue manager {1} could not be immediately released.
Message.Explanation: A broker profile could not be immediately deleted when the user issued a deletion request, because there were active subscriptions associated with the broker profile.
Message.UserResponse: No action is necessary, the system will automatically request that the subscriptions be deactivated then it will try again later.
